(7) After considering the application referred to in subsection (4) and any objection thereto, the Board may— (a) confirm the proposed variation or alteration, as the case may be, to which the application relates; (b) order that the proposed variation or alteration, as the case may be, to which the application relates shall not be made; or (c) order the operator of the undertaking to make such other variation or alteration, as the case may be, as the Board considers fit.
